            <Title>Items</Title>
            <Text>Limits/Rules
Item Set cumulative bonuses apply to every item owned in the set AFTER the first.  So cumulative bonuses are granted starting with the second item equipped.

Only one Fingerclaw per hand (arm in the code) may be equipped at a time.

Only ONE may be equipped at a time:
	Whistle
	Necklace
	Beard
	Leaf
	Sheet (grouped with Covers) (Cloak/Robe/etc)
	Charm
	Brooch
	Pin
	Tuning Fork

Duplicate items do not combine bonuses.

+/- % Magic Chance is a percent adjustment to the chance that a spell/song/alchemy works or takes effect.  Note, that most sorcerer’s spells work every time, and so Magic Chance does no effect them, but most magical bard song’s effect on on creatures is not guaranteed to work every time, so Magic Chance is applied.

+/- % Magic Effect is a percent adjustment to the amount of effect that a spell/song/alchemy has if it takes effect.  Even though there is a separate trait for Bless Effect and Curse Effect, Magic Effect still applies (and is combined) to Blessing and Cursing.

***Does Bless/Curse Chance mean ‘chance to cast success’ or ‘chance effected by’?…Let’s say ‘chance to cast success’.  If you want to be less effected by Bless/Curse then -% Bless/Curse effect.  There is no Bless Resist.  If you want a trait to make Bless less likely to take effect, then you are out of luck.  The closest you can get is a negative percent adjustment to the Blessing’s effects, with -% Bless Effect.


Types
There are four item Types: Fire, Frost, Honor, and Shadow, with eight valid combinations.  Only equipment (items that can be equipped) can be typed.  If an item’s name ends in one of the eight qualifying type names: “of &lt;Fire/Frost Honor/Shadow&gt;”, and it is equipped, then it confers Type based bonuses, specified below:

If item is &lt;Material&gt;: for weapons: 10% + 5x material based +% &lt;Type&gt; damage, for armor: 4% + 1/1.5x material based +% &lt;Type&gt; resist
If item is NOT Material: for weapons +50% &lt;Type&gt; damage, for armor: +13% &lt;Type&gt; resist


